import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---
{/* DRAFT pending attorney review — engaged pre-launch per TODO Phase 1 */}
<Base
  title="Privacy Policy — AdaptiveResume"
  description="What AdaptiveResume collects, how your resume is protected, why the AI never sees your name, how long we keep things, and how to delete everything in one action."
>
  <article class="section">
    <div class="container narrow">
      <p class="eyebrow">Legal</p>
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Your resume is some of the most personal data there is — your whole working life on a page.
        Here's exactly what we collect, what we do with it, who touches it, how long we keep it,
        and how to delete it.
      </p>
      <p class="effective">Effective date: 07/05/2026</p>

      <div class="prose">
        {/* ATTORNEY: entity name amendment is currently filing with the Georgia Secretary of State.
             Confirm the final registered entity string ("AdaptiveResume LLC") before publication. */}
        <p>
          <strong>AdaptiveResume LLC</strong>, a Georgia single-member limited liability company
          based in Marietta, Georgia ("AdaptiveResume," "we," "us"), operates the AdaptiveResume
          website and service (the "Service"). This policy is part of our
          <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>.
        </p>

        <h2>What we collect</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Account information:</strong> your email address and sign-in data.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Content you upload:</strong> up to three resumes and, optionally, a PDF of your
            own LinkedIn profile. These naturally contain your name, contact details, work history,
            employers, education, and credentials.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Your confirmations:</strong> your answers during the guided review — which
            proposed skills and credentials you confirmed, edited, or skipped.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Payment information:</strong> handled by <strong>Stripe</strong>. We receive
            confirmation of payment and limited billing metadata; <strong>we never receive or store
            your card number.</strong>
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Usage data:</strong> basic technical information (device, browser, pages used)
            needed to operate and improve the Service.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          We never scrape LinkedIn or any other platform. Profile data enters the Service only as a
          file you export and upload yourself.
        </p>

        <h2>The AI never sees your name</h2>
        <p>
          Before any of your resume content is sent to an AI model, we separate your personal
          identifiers — name, email, phone number, and links — from the resume text. The AI works
          on the de-identified text only, and your identifiers are re-attached only when your final
          document is assembled. <strong>The AI model never receives your name or contact
          details.</strong>
        </p>

        <h2>How we use your information</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>To provide the Service: build, review, and deliver your resume and, on the targeted build, your job-posting match read and interview-prep materials.</li>
          <li>To process payment, provide support, and send service-related messages.</li>
          <li>To keep the Service secure, prevent fraud and abuse, and comply with law.</li>
          <li>To improve the Service through the de-identified learning described below.</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Who processes your data for us</h2>
        <p>
          We share the minimum necessary data with a short list of providers that process it on our
          behalf under contract:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Anthropic (AI model API):</strong> processes de-identified resume text to
            produce the suggestions you review. API inputs and outputs are not used to train
            Anthropic's models, and retention is transient.
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Supabase (database and authentication hosting, United States):</strong> stores
            your account and content.
          </li>
          <li><strong>Stripe (payments):</strong> handles all card processing.</li>
          <li>
            <strong>Google (optional sign-in only):</strong> used only if you choose to sign in
            with Google.
          </li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          These providers may use your data only to provide their service to us. Beyond them, we
          share information only if required by law, to protect our rights or users, or in
          connection with a business transfer — and always subject to this policy.
          <strong>We do not sell your personal information, and we never share it with
          employers.</strong>
        </p>

        <h2>How we learn without keeping "you"</h2>
        <p>
          To get better at finding what people in your line of work tend to leave off, we keep
          <strong>de-identified observations</strong>: confirmed skill and terminology patterns
          together with the employer name, role title, and work location they came from —
          <strong>never your name or contact details.</strong> These observations are retained
          indefinitely, because they are what makes the Service smarter for the next person in a
          role like yours. They describe roles and workplaces, not people; they cannot be traced
          back to you and are not removed when you delete your account.
        </p>
        {/* ATTORNEY: the 06/19/2026 internal draft offered an opt-out from learning contributions;
             the current product retains de-identified observations without an opt-out. Please
             confirm this posture is defensible under CCPA/CPRA (de-identified-data standard,
             Cal. Civ. Code 1798.140(m)) and whether an opt-out or additional disclosure is needed. */}

        <h2>How we protect it</h2>
        <ul>
          <li>Resume content is stored encrypted at rest (AES-256-GCM).</li>
          <li>Sessions are encrypted.</li>
          <li>Multi-factor authentication is available to every account.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          No method of transmission or storage is perfectly secure, but we treat your resume with
          the care we'd want for our own.
        </p>

        <h2>How long we keep things</h2>
        {/* ATTORNEY: all four retention windows below are PROPOSED, not yet operating history.
             Please confirm each is appropriate before publication. */}
        <ul>
          <li>
            <strong>Uploaded source files</strong> (your original resumes and LinkedIn PDF) are
            deleted after your build completes — 30 days at the most.
            {/* ATTORNEY: confirm the 30-day maximum for source uploads. */}
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>In-progress review drafts</strong> auto-delete after 7 days if a build isn't
            completed.
            {/* ATTORNEY: confirm the 7-day auto-delete for abandoned drafts. */}
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Finished resumes</strong> are stored for 12 months so you can re-download them,
            then deleted with notice to you.
            {/* ATTORNEY: confirm the 12-month window and the notice-before-deletion mechanism. */}
          </li>
          <li>
            <strong>Purchase and build records</strong> are kept for 7 years for tax and accounting
            purposes.
            {/* ATTORNEY: confirm the 7-year financial-records window with the CPA as well. */}
          </li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Deleting your data</h2>
        <p>
          You can delete your account yourself, any time, with a single "delete my account" action
          — it removes all of your personal data in one step. Two exceptions:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>financial records held by Stripe (which we're required to retain), and</li>
          <li>the de-identified observations described above, which contain nothing that identifies you.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          <strong>We honor CCPA rights for everyone, regardless of what state you live in:</strong>
          the right to know what we hold about you, to correct it, to delete it, to get a portable
          copy, and to never be discriminated against for exercising those rights. Email
          <a href="mailto:support@adaptiveresume.com">support@adaptiveresume.com</a> and we'll
          respond within the time the law requires.
        </p>

        <h2>No ads, no tracking, no sale</h2>
        <p>
          We do not sell personal information. We do not use third-party advertising or third-party
          tracking. We do not use your data for cross-context behavioral advertising.
        </p>
        {/* ATTORNEY: first-party conversion analytics is planned (no third-party trackers).
             Please advise whether a cookie/consent banner is required for that configuration
             given the U.S.-focused audience. */}

        <h2>Cookies</h2>
        <p>
          We use essential cookies for sign-in and security. That's it today. If that changes,
          this policy will be updated first.
        </p>

        <h2>Children</h2>
        <p>
          The Service is for adults 18 and over. We do not knowingly collect data from minors. If
          you believe a minor has used the Service, contact us and we will delete the data.
        </p>

        <h2>Where your data lives</h2>
        {/* ATTORNEY: EU/UK users are not currently targeted; no GDPR transfer mechanism is in
             place. Confirm whether the consent-to-U.S.-processing statement below is sufficient,
             or whether access from the EU/UK should be addressed differently. */}
        <p>
          We operate in the United States and process data here. If you access the Service from
          outside the U.S., you consent to processing in the U.S.
        </p>

        <h2>Changes</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this policy prospectively, posting a new effective date and, for material
          changes, giving you notice. Continued use after changes means you accept the updated
          policy.
        </p>

        <h2>Contact</h2>
        <p>
          AdaptiveResume LLC · Marietta, Georgia<br />
          <a href="mailto:support@adaptiveresume.com">support@adaptiveresume.com</a>
        </p>
      </div>

      <nav class="legal-links" aria-label="Other legal pages">
        <span class="muted">Related:</span>
        <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>
        <a href="/disclaimer">Disclaimer</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </article>

